<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Buses will replace Tube services on the Jubilee line between Waterloo and Neasden on Saturday and Sunday 25 and 26 June 2005 while track replacement works are undertaken.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>This will improve the reliability and give a smoother ride on the Jubilee line.</p>
<p>The Jubilee line will therefore be operating in two separate sections between Stratford and Waterloo and between Neasden and Stanmore while Tube Lines carry out this work.</p>
<p>The Metropolitan line will also be suspended south of Wembley Park on the same weekend.</p>
<p>Rail Replacement Bus Services</p>
<p><strong>Bus service A</strong><br>Baker Street to Willesden Green calling at all Jubilee line stations</p>
<p><strong>Bus service B</strong> <br>Willesden Green to Wembley Park calling at Dollis Hill, but not Neasden Station</p>
<p><strong>Bus service C</strong><br>Non-stop Wembley Park to Stonebridge Park</p>
<p>London Underground tickets and passes will be valid on the local bus routes to reach alternative London Underground lines.</p>
<p>Passengers are advised to start their journeys at least 30 minutes earlier. </p>
<p>For 24-hour information on all London travel, please call: 020 7222 1234 or visit <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk">TfL's website</a>.<br></p>
            <ul>
<li>TfL is investing &pound;10 billion over the next five years to improve and expand London's transport network, over half of that in the Tube</li>
<li>Tube Lines are responsible for the maintenance and renewal of the Jubilee, Northern and Piccadilly lines</li>
<li>For further information, please call the TfL Press Office on 020 7941 4434.<br></li></ul>

     

        
        
        
